# Quality bar for the full uplift

## Testing expectations
Every meaningful API addition should have:
- focused unit coverage where relevant
- parity coverage where Java parity exists
- runtime/integration coverage where behavior matters
- canonical scenario proof where the API is orchestration-heavy

## Verification gate
Run and keep green:
- `npm install`
- `npx tsc -p libs/sdk-dsl/tsconfig.lib.json --noEmit`
- `npx tsc -p libs/sdk-dsl/tsconfig.spec.json --noEmit`
- `npx eslint libs/sdk-dsl`
- `npx vitest run --config libs/sdk-dsl/vite.config.ts`
- `npx vite build --config libs/sdk-dsl/vite.config.ts`

## Commit discipline
After each coherent stage:
- review changes critically
- fix obvious issues before moving on
- commit with a conventional commit message
- keep subject line <= 72 chars

## Public-repo hygiene
If `references/**` are present, they are development-only.
Final committed public repo artifacts must not depend on those references.

## Completion bar
The whole uplift is complete only when the scorecard reaches 9–10/10 in all categories and all stages are either complete or explicitly deferred with justification.
